structure.unit: Registration Of Certain Professions And Occupations

law.catch_line: Register; Annual Reports; Investigation Of Complaints
law.text: The board shall keep a register of all veterinarians registered by it, which shall be open to public inspection, and shall make an annual report. It shall investigate all complaints of the violation of any provision of section fifty-nine and of section sixty-five, so far as it relates to veterinary medicine, and report the same to the proper prosecuting officers.
